  %h3 Privacy Policy

  %h5 What this Privacy Policy Covers

  %p
    This policy covers how Tranact treats personal information that Tranact collects and receives, including information related to your past use of 
    Tranact products and services/software business. Personal and business information is information about you that is personally identifiable like names, 
    addresses, email addresses, or phone numbers, and that is not otherwise publicly available.

  %h5 
    This policy does not apply to the practices of companies that Tranact does not own or control, or to people that Tranact does not employ or manage. 
    In addition, certain companies associated with Tranact have their own privacy statements that we do not control.

  %h5 Information Collection and Use
   
  %h5 General
  
  %p
    Tranact collects personal information when you register with Tranact, when you use Tranact product and services and software, and when you enter certain 
    information into the Tranact system. Tranact may combine information we have with information we obtain from other sources. We may ask for information 
    such as your name, address, email address, birth date, gender, zip code, occupation, and personal interests. For some financial products and services 
    we may also ask for your Social Security  number  or  Taxpayer Identification Number, and information about your assets.

  %p
    Tranact collects information about your transactions with us, including information about your use of financial, products and services that we offer. 
    Tranact may automatically receives and records information on our server logs from your browser, including your IP address, Tranact cookie information, 
    and the page you request.

  %p
    Your Internet service provider may automatically provide information about you to our web server, such as its web site address and possibly your email 
    address. We may collect information that you send to us in an e-mail message and information that you submit to us in a script based form.

  %p
    Email sent to us may not be secure. If you choose to send us an email message, you are consenting to our unencrypted retention of the content of the email, 
    your email address, and our response.

  %p
    Tranact uses information for the following general purposes: to customize the content you see, fulfill your request for products, services and software, 
    improve our services, contact you, conduct research, and provide anonymous reporting for internal and external clients.

  %p
    Tranact does not rent, sell, or share personal information about you with other people or nonaffiliated companies except to provide products or services 
    you requested, or under the following circumstances:

    %ul
      %li
        We provide the information to trusted partners who work on behalf of or with Tranact under confidentiality agreements. These companies may use your 
        personal information to help Tranact communicate with you about offers from Tranact and our marketing partners. These companies, however, do not have 
        any independent right to share this information.

      %li
        We respond to subpoenas, court orders, or legal process, or to establish or exercise our legal rights or defend against legal claims;

      %li
        We believe it is necessary to share information in order to investigate, prevent or take action regarding illegal activities, suspected fraud, 
        situations involving potential threats to the physical safety of any person, violations of Tranact terms of use, or as otherwise required by law.

      %li
        We may transfer information about you if Tranact is acquired by or merged with another company. In this event, we must notify you if such acquiring 
        company will change this privacy policy, and such change in this policy does not conform to the Agreement.

      %li
        If Tranact desires to change or modify this privacy policy, and such change or modification is not in conformance with the Agreement, 
        then Tranact agrees not to change this privacy policy without the express written consent of the Customer.
  
  %p
    We reserve the right to send you certain communications relating to the Tranact service, such as service announcements and administrative messages that are 
    considered part of your Tranact account without offering you the opportunity to opt-out of receiving them.

  %h5 Confidentiality and Security

  %p
    We limit access to personal information about you to employees and independent contractors who we believe reasonably need to come into contact with that 
    information to provide products or services to you or in order to perform services.

  %p
    We have physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards that to protect personal information about you.

  %h5 Changes to this Privacy Policy

  %p
    Tranact may update this policy. We may notify you about significant changes in the way we treat personal information by sending a notice to the primary email 
    address specified in your Tranact account and optionally by placing a prominent notice on our site.

  %h5 Questions and Suggestions

  %p
    If you have questions or suggestions, please complete a feedback form or you can contact us at: 
